DevOps Engineer: looking for a highly skilled Redhat openshift DevOps Engineer to streamline and automate our software development and deployment processes. The ideal candidate will be responsible for ensuring smooth CI/CD pipelines, managing cloud infrastructure, and optimizing system performance for our financial technology solutions.
Key Responsibilities:
CI/CD Implementation & Automation:
• Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines for automated builds, testing, and deployments.
• Work with development teams to integrate code changes smoothly and efficiently.
Infrastructure as Code (IaC):
• Use Terraform, Ansible, or similar tools to automate infrastructure provisioning.
• Manage cloud-based and on-premise infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP).
Monitoring & Performance Optimization:
• Set up and manage monitoring tools (Prometheus, Grafana, ELK Stack, etc.).
• Identify and troubleshoot performance issues to ensure system reliability.
Security & Compliance:
• Implement security best practices in cloud and on-prem environments.
• Conduct regular audits to ensure compliance with industry standards.
Collaboration & Support:
• Work closely with developers, QA, and IT teams to optimize workflows.
• Provide support for production and non-production environments.
Required Skills & Qualifications:
Technical Skills:
• Hands-on experience with CI/CD tools (Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI/CD).
• Strong knowledge of Kubernetes, Docker, and containerization.
• Expertise in cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP).
• Proficiency in scripting (Bash, Python, or Shell).
• Experience with Infrastructure as Code (Terraform, Ansible, CloudFormation).
• Knowledge of logging and monitoring tools (Splunk, ELK Stack, Prometheus).
Soft Skills:
• Strong problem-solving abilities and analytical thinking.
• Excellent communication and teamwork skills.
